--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Getting Input from a File

1. Read data from a file:
	# <command> < inputfile

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Getting User Input

1. Get input from the user:
	# read
   Note: User input will be placed into the shell variable REPLY!
   or:
	# read â€“ p "<prompt_string>" VARIABLE
   or:
	# read VARIABLE1 VARIABLE2 VARIABLE3

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Prompting for a Password

1. Prompt the user for a passwor:
	# read -s -p "<prompt_string>" PASSWD; printf "%b" "\n"

2. Return terminal session to sanity:
	# stty sane

